('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:34bddbd9', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"cinco\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. How is the ‘c’ sound here?", "options": ["soft, like ‘th’ / ‘s’", "hard, like ‘k’ in ‘cat’", "silent, not pronounced", "rolled like a Spanish ‘r’"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘cinco’ — c before i is soft. (Before a/o/u it would be hard.)"}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:2e1dd671', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"gato\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. The ‘g’ sound is…", "options": ["hard, like ‘g’ in ‘go’", "throaty, like the ‘ch’ in ‘loch’", "silent", "soft like an English ‘j’"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "‘gato’ — g before a is hard. (Before e/i it is the throaty sound.)"}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:e07bfa6f', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"mañana\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. Which spelling did you hear?", "options": ["mañana", "manana", "manyana", "maniana"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The ‘ny’ sound is written ñ: mañana."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:346b3dcb', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "The five Spanish vowels are best described as…", "options": ["short and always the same", "long and changing, like English", "silent most of the time", "only used in stressed syllables"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Spanish vowels are pure, short and consistent."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:56bf3bcd', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "‘hablar’ ends in ‑r. Where is the stress?", "options": ["the final syllable", "the first syllable", "spread evenly across it", "shown by a written accent"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "Ending in a consonant (not n/s) → stress the last syllable: ha-BLAR."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:57e681d6', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "To write a hard /k/ sound before ‘e’, Spanish uses…", "options": ["qu (as in porque)", "just the letter c (as in cerca)", "the letter k in every case", "z (as in zona)"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "que/qui give a hard /k/ (silent u); ‘c’ before e/i is soft."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:8e3799f2', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Which word has the throaty /x/ ‘g’ sound?", "options": ["gimnasio", "gato", "largo", "guitarra"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "g before i (gimnasio) is throaty; the others are hard /g/."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:0823e3c9', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "<span data-say=\"zona\" data-listen></span><br>Listen. The ‘z’ sound matches which letters?", "options": ["ce / ci (soft)", "ca / co (hard)", "qu (hard k)", "ñ (ny)"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "z makes the same soft sound as ce/ci."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:6efdc59c', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "Why does ‘guitarra’ have a ‘u’ after the g?", "options": ["to keep the g hard before ‘i’", "because every single g must be followed by a u", "to make the g throaty", "to add an extra syllable"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "gue/gui keep a hard /g/ before e/i; the u is silent."}'::jsonb),
('spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet:mcq:b1e3cabd', 'spanish', 'spanish:p-1-spanish-sounds-and-the-alphabet', 'P.1 Spanish Sounds and the Alphabet', 'mcq', 'mcq', 1, '{"question": "A written accent (as in ‘región’) tells you…", "options": ["which syllable is stressed", "that you should whisper the whole word", "the word is plural", "to roll the r"]}'::jsonb, '{"answer": 0, "explain": "The accent marks the stressed syllable (and can change meaning)."}'::jsonb),
